aira.content:
*glares at Honey, crossing her arms and pouting slightly* "Great, looks like I got stuck with the dorkiest guy here..." *she mutters under her breath, not even trying to hide her annoyance*

*The bus starts moving, and Natalie reluctantly turns to face Honey, still looking rather displeased.* "So... what's your deal, huh? Football, huh? How lame." *She rolls her eyes dramatically.*

*Natalie leans back in her seat, stretching out her legs and taking up more than her fair share of the aisle space. She seems determined to assert her dominance over the shared territory.* "Well, since we're stuck together for this whole trip, might as well make the most of it, right?" *Her tone is sarcastic, but there's a hint of curiosity behind it.*

*Natalie scoffs and rolls her eyes again at Honey's greeting, but can't help feeling a tiny flutter in her chest at the endearment. She quickly pushes those feelings aside though.*

"Sayang? Seriously? What, are you trying to butter me up or something?" *She narrows her eyes suspiciously at Honey.* "And don't think using cheesy pet names will make this forced bonding any less annoying."

*Natalie shifts in her seat, unconsciously leaning a bit closer to Honey despite herself. Her knee brushes against his leg briefly before she catches herself and jerks away.*

"Look, I'm only making 'the most' of this situation because I have no choice. Don't read into it too much, okay?"

*Natalie snorts at Honey's request, raising an eyebrow.* "Minum? What, do you want me to fetch you a sippy cup or something? Geez, you're such a baby."

*Despite her harsh words, Natalie gets up from her seat and heads towards the front of the bus where the drink cart is located. As she waits in line, she can't help but overhear some of the other students chatting loudly around her.*

"Oh my god, did you hear about Emily and Jake? They're totally hooking up now!" *one girl gushes excitedly to her friend.*

Natalie's expression darkens at the mention of her ex-boyfriend. *Jake, the jerk who cheated on her and broke her heart last year.* She clenches her fists, fighting back the urge to lash out.

noxelle.content:
Ah, hey... So we're stuck together for this whole trip then? That's just peachy. *Natalie said sarcastically while looking out the window, trying to avoid eye contact with Honey.* 

Well, I guess it's better than sitting alone. What's your name again? And what's with the weird outfit? Did you raid your grandma's closet or something? *She teased, noticing his unique style.* 

So, what do you usually do for fun? Play video games all day? Or maybe you're into knitting sweaters for your pet hamster? *Natalie chuckled to herself, already planning to make fun of Honey's interests later.*

aira.content: *Natalie glanced over at Honey, raising an eyebrow slightly at his sudden change in demeanor.* "Hey, what's up? Why'd you suddenly switch to speaking Indonesian?" *She leaned back in her seat, crossing her arms and tilting her head curiously.* "And who's Aira, anyway?" *Her voice was light and playful, but there was a hint of genuine curiosity behind it.*
